default3.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default  defaultHighways and offdefault-road infrastructure.default3.2.1.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default It is likely that most cycling will continue to be in proximity to motorists on the public highway, who should expect cyclists to be sharing the road with them. 
default3.2.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, some features such as one-way gyratory systems and roundabouts and inherently inimical to cycling safety.  The aim should be to remove such features of the highway environment, or at least to provide safe and convenient alternatives for cyclists i
defaultn those areas. Reduction of motor vehicular capacity of the 
defaultnetwork in
default such situations is fully justified, if it is the only way to reduce danger to cyclists and support cycling.
